<p>Thousands of people marched in Tunis on Saturday to denounce repression and call for the release of detainees and a return to democracy [aljazeera#1][straitstimes#1][timesofisrael#1][newarab#1]. Protesters accused President Kais Saied of consolidating one-man rule and using the judiciary and police to silence critics amid economic hardship [straitstimes#1][newarab#1][timesofisrael#1]. Observers noted echoes of Tunisia’s Arab Spring-era uprising, with demonstrators also demanding accountability [timesofisrael#1].</p><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Large turnout: Thousands rallied in the capital on Saturday [aljazeera#1][straitstimes#1][timesofisrael#1][newarab#1]</li><li>Core demands: Demonstrators called for freeing jailed critics and political prisoners, ending repression, and restoring democratic norms with greater accountability [aljazeera#1][timesofisrael#1][newarab#1][straitstimes#1]</li><li>Allegations of overreach: Protesters and opposition figures accused President Kais Saied of cementing one-man rule and using the judiciary and police to curb dissent [straitstimes#1][newarab#1]</li><li>Economic strain: Economic hardship was cited alongside shrinking freedoms as a driver of public anger and participation [timesofisrael#1]</li><li>Echoes of 2011: The demonstration was described as echoing the Arab Spring [timesofisrael#1]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Protesters in Tunis: Called for releasing detainees, ending repression, and restoring democratic governance [aljazeera#1][newarab#1] (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/23/enough-repression-thousands-of-tunisians-protest-against-kais-saied'>Al Jazeera; The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Opposition and activists: Accused Kais Saied of consolidating one-man rule and using the judiciary and police to silence critics [straitstimes#1][newarab#1] (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/tunisians-escalate-protests-against-saied-demanding-return-of-democracy'>The Straits Times; The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Observers: Noted echoes of the Arab Spring amid shrinking freedoms and economic hardship [timesofisrael#1] (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/tunisians-protest-against-political-and-economic-conditions-in-echo-of-arab-spring/'>The Times of Israel</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/23/enough-repression-thousands-of-tunisians-protest-against-kais-saied'>‘Enough repression’: Thousands of Tunisians protest against Kais Saied</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/tunisians-escalate-protests-against-saied-demanding-return-of-democracy'>Tunisians escalate protests against Saied, demanding return of democracy</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/tunisians-protest-against-political-and-economic-conditions-in-echo-of-arab-spring/'>Tunisians protest against political and economic conditions, in echo of Arab Spring</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/tunisians-escalate-protests-against-saied-demanding-democracy'>Tunisians escalate protests against Saied, demanding democracy</a> - newarab.com</li></ul>